This paper deals with Bayesian machine learning and sampling from distributions, which are common topics in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses Markov chains and their mixing times, which are relevant to the subfield of information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper introduces novel techniques for proving spectral gaps, which are relevant to the subfield of numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also deals with decomposing the stationary measure as a mixture of distributions, which is relevant to the subfield of data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the use of simulated tempering, which is relevant to the subfield of control systems (cs.SY).
